Package model

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Button
    The Button is an element which appears in the labyrinth and allows to open a path in it.
    Candy
    The Candy is an element which appears in the labyrinth and can be taken to increase the score.
    Character
    The abstract class Character is a superclass of all classes that can move on the labyrinth.
    Colision
    This class handles the colision between Element type objects.
    Door
    The Door is an element which appears in the labyrinth and allows to create a new labyrinth to continue to play after you passed it.
    Edge
    Class representing the edge of a graph.
    EdgeTest
    JUnit test class for the Edge class.
    Element
    The abstract class Element is a superclass of all classes that appears in the labyrinth.
    Enemy
    The Enemy is an element which appears in the labyrinth and tries to kill the player.
    Game  
    Labyrinth
    Create the graph representing the labyrinth using the SimpleGraph class.
    LabyrinthTest
    JUnit test class for the Labyrinth class.
    Player
    The player is a character that moves around in the labyrinth.
    PlayerTest
    PlayerTest is used to test collisionWall(...) and moves(...) with a specific labyrinth.
    Score
    Class handling the scoring element of the game
    Vertex
    Class representing a vertex in a graph.
    VertexTest
    JUnit test class for the Vertex class.
